Rainfall in the past few days has easedthe threat of drought in the south China province of Guangdong,the New China News Agency said.    It said 75 pct of early rice fields are ready to be plantedand seedlings have already been transplanted on 90 pct of ricefields in Hainan island. Some 840,000 hectares of farmland havebeen planted with cash crops including sugar cane, peanuts andsoybeans, 67,000 ha more than in 1986.    The provincial government has increased investment in grainand taken effective measures to combat natural disasters thisyear, the agency said, but gave no further details. REUTER&#3;